widgets_values: You can use any pre-processor you'd like, I'm using Depth here. DWPose, Canny, Lineart, all work as expected.

I am using Depth and Lineart for this example, but you can use any combination of the ones provided. You can also bypass the image blend node and connect one of the preprocessor nodes straight to "Resize Image" if you don't want to use Image Blend.
You can use any pre-processor you'd like, I'm using Depth here. DWPose, Canny, Lineart, all work as expected.

Just upload a video, make sure the video is resized appropriately, adjust your model paths appropriately in all model nodes, and go! Using SDXL, this takes about 10GB VRAM max without any quantizations.

With flux, it takes about 20GB, unforutnately due to the size of flux Union controlnet.

If you want to run 1-click generations, use SDXL, if you want a little better quality, use flux.

On my 5090, generations take about 2.5minutes
